title.label: The Greatest Game Ever To Grace The IPhone! (By Tyler Timko)

content.label:
Forget Raid Shadow Legends and Super Mario Run, forget Angry Birds and Candy Crush. Tiny Wings is one of the most calming, challenging and artistically sound games ever to release onto the AppStore. It’s seems like a simple concept, use momentum Sonic the Hedgehog style to slide down slopes to reach new islands before the sun goes down, right? But it’s much more in depth than that! The islands are always changing, meaning you can never memorize the islands exactly as you played them! Plus there are the loads of challenges to do in the day trip mode! (My favorite is Holding your Phone upside down until island 5!) And the fun just keeps coming with Chapter 2: Flight School! Where you can choose from one of 4 birds, (Which you can name!) and race against computer opponents though 5 islands with multiple race tracks in each! And scoring well in the races gives you new nests with different colors plus additional score multipliers! Despite this game coming out in 2011 and not receiving to many updates since 2015, this game remains one of the best mobile apps on the market! There’s not an overwhelming amount of micro transactions, there’s no pay to win, there’s no ads, and most importantly the game is actually fun to play! This game deserves all the praise it gets and I hope anyone reading this review picks up the game either for the first time, or to look back at a game they played earlier in the iPhones life! The art and music, combined with the clever and rewarding gameplay makes this hands down, the GREATEST GAME on this entire App Store!!! Among all the knock off games, and bad games in general, this game stands like a shining star of what an Mobile game SHOULD be!! 

An instant 5 stars in my book!

title.label: Amazing game with a few flaws

content.label: First off, this game has been my go to game for years now. I love the flying mechanic and thatFeeling of soaring through the air. As much as I’d like to see this game is flawless I have a few points of feedback for the DEVS.The first one is that the handicap feature in the multiplayer mode is broken. My sister and I have been playing and it is extremely easy to cheat by letting the other person win and get a big handicap and then coming in and beating them. Another way it is kind of over powered is when someone has a bad first round and the other person gets a major handicap that lasts throughout the game even when you guys are very close his skill level. Another way this game could be improved would be to add a multiplayer feature where you could play with people around the globe. I’ve always wondered how I would do against other people and I think this would be a really fun addition to the game. Another game mode could also be added The one that Some of the birds might have different features such as charged up abilities and sabotaging abilities. I think this would be a great implementation to a new game mode but I wouldn’t wanna ruin nostalgia by adding this to all of the other game modes as well. Thanks so much for making this amazing game! :-)
